INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('5843', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 27b580c281be8d0769dcabd54b026c11', '<p>Once you have completed your payment and have received your payment receipt, your company name will be considered as âreservedâ. You now have to wait until your company name is reviewed and approved by the authorities. Once it is confirmed, your name is reserved for three months for you to register your business within this period. If you need more time to register, you can pay a fee and extend the reservation for another 3 months.</p><p>Â </p><p>You can also check the status of your registration at any time at the bottom of the screen. At this stage you will see in âmy unfinished businessâ that your company name is waiting for approval. Once your request is approved, you will receive an email and a new dashboard will appear. You are now ready to register !</p><p>Â </p><p>To register your business you need to fill in your personal and business information, as well as upload the required documents. Once you receive the approval of registration, you will be able to print your certificate of incorporation, which means you are registered as a company at the Ministry of Commerce.</p><p>Â </p><p>Note that from the moment you start your application, you have 15 days to complete it, otherwise you will need to begin the application process again.</p><p>Â </p><p>If you want to register a limited company (private/public) or a foreign company.</p><p>Choose âCompaniesâ and then âIncorporate a Private Limited Company/Incorporate a Public Limited Companyâ in the left menu. You will have to fill in the following sections.</p><p>Â </p><p>Step 1: Your business</p><p>General details</p><p>Â </p><p>Check the box âselect a reserve nameâ and then chose the name of the company (that you already reserved) in the âdrop-down barâ.</p><p>Upload your memorandum and articles of association</p><p>Business activities</p><p>Â </p><p>Define your business objective. This is the general activity of your company. Business objectives are associated with codes and proposed in the drop-down bar. You just have to pick the one which fits best with your company objective.</p><p>Define your main business activities. They are more precise than the business objective and again choose the one that is most appropriate in the drop-down bar.</p><p>Share par value</p><p>Â </p><p>You have to write your share par value in both USD and riel. This will be in your Memorandum &amp; Articles of Association</p><p>Number of employees</p><p>Â </p><p>You need to give the number of male and female employees</p><p>Then you need to give both the number of Cambodian employees and number of foreign employees</p><p>âEmployee position detailsâ have to be uploaded. Please refer to our template and fill it with the information about your staff</p><p>Any supporting documents that you think may be appropriate can also be uploaded</p><p>Â </p><p>VIDEO</p><p>Â </p><p>Step 2: Addresses</p><p>Fill the details of your office address and upload your proof of location on the same page</p><p>Tick the box if the postal address is the same as your office address.</p><p>Provide your email address and your phone number.</p><p>Â </p><p>VIDEO</p><p>Â </p><p>Step 3: Directors</p><p>If you are one of the directors, you can push the âadd me as a directorâ button, then your information will be automatically filled for the page. If you are not one of the directors, then you should manually fill the information of the directors.</p><p>Â </p><p>Chose the proof of identity you want to use (passport or ID) and give its details. Then upload the proof of ID you already scanned.</p><p>Â </p><p>Tick the box if you are the chairman of the Board of Directors. The chairman means the most senior person in the business.</p><p>Â </p><p>Tick the âconsent boxâ that insures you have not been convicted for any crime and that all the information you provided is true.</p><p>Â </p><p>Upload the director consent. This letter proves you have no criminal background signed by the director of your company (see our template on this link)</p><p>Â </p><p>Then you can add another directorâs details if there is another one.</p><p>Â </p><p>VIDEO</p><p>Â </p><p>Step 4: Shares &amp; shareholders</p><p>âMore than one class of shareâ Yes/no. For most companies, this will be no, if you are unsure, then select no</p><p>Â </p><p>Select in the drop-down bar if the shareholder is an individual</p><p>Â </p><p>If one of the directors you gave information about are part of the shareholders, then tick the box âselect from the list of directorsâ and select him/her. The information you already filled will be automatically saved. You can also add yourself as a shareholder, by pushing the corresponding button</p><p>Â </p><p>If shareholders are not directors or yourself, please fill in the information. You can also add another shareholder by pushing the button at the end. Every time you add a shareholder, it is asked how many shares each of them owns and you will need to upload their proof of ID.</p><p>Â </p><p>After you have added every shareholder, select the nationality of the majority shareholders, as well as the percentage of the majority shareholders.</p><p>Â </p><p>Step 5: Review the information</p><p>You have now filled all the necessary information for your application, you will need to review the information and be sure that it is all correct and all required documents are uploaded. Click on the icon buttons at the top to modify.</p><p>DO NOT SUBMIT YOUR APPLICATION YET.</p><p>Â </p><p>If you HAVE an ACLEDA bank accountâ¦</p><p>Â </p><p>Click on âsubmitâ to confirm your application, you will get access to ACLEDA pop-up page</p><p>Â </p><p>Select payment preferences</p><p>Give account details</p><p>Request an OTP number (you will have to write a 6 digit-number that you will receive on your mobile phone upon request)</p><p>Once you see the transaction result, go âback to merchantâ</p><p>Save or print your payment receipt which appears</p><p>If you DO NOT HAVE an ACLEDA bank account but another account in any other bankâ¦</p><p>Â </p><p>Do not submit your application, but click on âSave and exitâ when you are sure all the information is correct. From this moment, you have 15 days to pay and go to the Ministry of Commerce with your receipt, as they will only save your data for two weeks. If you do not do the payment within this period, you will have to do all the business registration steps again. Bring your payment receipt provided by the bank to the Department of Accounting and Finance (second building ground floor) at the Ministry of Commerce. The finance officer has to approve it before you can submit your online application.</p><p>Â </p><p>Process the payment by going to one of these banks. Here are the bank accounts of the Ministry of Commerce associated:</p><p>Â </p><p>FOREIGN TRADE BANK (FTB)</p><p>KHR: 010-01-290-000094-0</p><p>Â </p><p>USD: 010-30-063-000937-8</p><p>Â </p><p>CANADIA BANK</p><p>KHR: 001-000-333-88-22</p><p>Â </p><p>USD:001-000-333-55-88</p><p>Â </p><p>ACLEDA BANK</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '0c2f231c31fcb071460c15f4ea493a7e', '', NULL);
