INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6746', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 39569a2af868cfe83cb37b49a40dd348', '<p>For importing and exporting, you need to register your patent as an import/export patent when you register with the General Department of Tax.</p><p>When you are ready to do your first import/export you need to register with the Automated System for Customs Data (ASYCUDA). To do this you will need to go to the customs office located at No. 6-8, Preah Norodom Blvd., Sangkat Phsar Thmei III, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia.</p><p>If you are importing/exporting any items deemed sensitive by the government then you will need to obtain a licence from the relevant ministry.Â </p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '9c907f065d0f80b918c96785f1d01590', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6747', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - f861d3b6a0c1e1324ad0dfcea4d2908c', '<p><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0px;\">Note that from the moment you start your application, you have 15 days to complete it, otherwise you will need to begin the application process again.</span></p><p>If you want to register a limited company (private/public) or a foreign company.</p><p>Choose âCompaniesâ and then âIncorporate a Private Limited Company/Incorporate a Public Limited Companyâ in the left menu. You will have to fill in the following sections.</p><p><strong>Step 1: Your business</strong></p><p><em>General details</em></p><ul><li>Check the box âselect a reserve nameâ and then chose the name of the company (that you already reserved) in the âdrop-down barâ.</li><li>Upload your memorandum and articles of association</li></ul><p><em>Business activities</em></p><ul><li>Define your business objective. This is the general activity of your company. Business objectives are associated with codes and proposed in the drop-down bar. You just have to pick the one which fits best with your company objective.</li><li>Define your main business activities. They are more precise than the business objective and again choose the one that is most appropriate in the drop-down bar.</li><li>Write your share par value in both USD and riel. This will be in your Memorandum &amp; Articles of Association</li><li>Provide the number of male and female employees and the number of Cambodian employees and number of foreign employees</li><li>âEmployee position detailsâ have to be uploaded. Please refer to our template and fill it with the information about your staff</li><li>Any supporting documents that you think may be appropriate can also be uploaded</li></ul><p><strong>Step 2: Addresses</strong></p><ul><li>Fill the details of your office address and upload your proof of location on the same page (property tax receipt)</li><li>Tick the box if the postal address is the same as your office address.</li><li>Provide your email address and your phone number.</li><li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">Â </li><li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">Below is a video from the Ministry of Commerce explaining how to use the online system</li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'eff112b49e7bdc1463c64cfed5668d15', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6748', 'en', 'elementor-1295', 'title-heading-32a3dbb', 'How to find Start Up Capital', '63', '1', 'h2', 'LINE', 'Heading', '10', '', '0303f8bb9c4f10e73a09cf2f23670574', 'optional', '6');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6749', 'en', 'elementor-1295', 'editor-text-editor-f1e96ef', '<p>When we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business</p>', '63', '2', '', 'VISUAL', 'Text editor', '10', '', '85c3a4e5a4c2b21a0cb0747c9f7bc6fd', 'optional', '45');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6750', 'en', 'elementor-1295', 'editor-text-editor-2674c50f', '<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start.Â </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our <a href=\"http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p>Â </p>', '63', '3', '', 'VISUAL', 'Text editor', '10', '', '7e3b1051d51a8e300b3f465d592b7123', 'optional', '313');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6751', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 73f56aaa57d1483060161685b3b00911', '<p>When we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '64ce34d63723655464f17ce0a2654208', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6752', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 9f5f6828eec464964e83e65df5b1064d', '<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start.Â </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our Funding Opportunities page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'f8dd9ca67f423f600c433f68b2f91c65', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6753', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 45dbabe2cd5eb1b86165540f2b96ee49', '<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start.Â </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our <a href=\"http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'b10131efc5cc5f008c979c59baf656b9', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6754', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 1302e5694979918e6d4b487a8eef4b76', '<p>Each month you will have to pay your taxes, this includes your value added tax (VAT), tax on salary, minimum tax on profit, withholding tax and public lighting tax. Additionally you will need to pay your NSSF fees (see here).</p><p>Filing and payment of taxes in Cambodia for medium and large taxpayers is quite complex, we highly recommend that you hire a professional to assist you in this process. However, it is important you understand the basic process, as its your responsibility to ensure that all the taxes are paid correctly.</p><p>For small taxpayers (sole proprietors and partnerships), you only need to fill out one form. The instructions are found on the second page of the form.</p><p>For medium and large taxpayers, there are multiple forms and evidence that is required.</p><p>To file your taxes you need to download the appropriate forms found here. You will need to fill out all the forms and provide the necessary evidence, you need to hand these forms in, with payment to your local tax department for your Khan. Monthly taxes are due on the 20<sup>th</sup> of each month.</p><p><a href=\"http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/tax-nssf-rates/\">For the latest tax rates, see here.</a></p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '604f580a467bfb240690c65f55920dcc', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6755', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - a420c354d6523836274ebb51e0d0e7c3', '<p><strong>1. Minimum Tax</strong></p><p>Profit tax prepayment:</p><p>Every month, you need to pay the rate of 1% on your turnover of the previous month inclusive of all taxes, except for VAT.</p><p><strong>2. Withholding Tax</strong></p><p>Rental : 10%</p><p>Labour : 15%</p><p><strong>3. Value Added Tax (VAT)</strong></p><p>The standard rate of VAT is 10%. It applies to all supplies, excluding exports and non-taxable supplies. Exported goods from Cambodia and services consumed outside Cambodia are not subject to VAT tax. The VAT is charged to the client and then paid to the government.</p><p><strong>4. Salary Tax and Tax on Fringe Benefit</strong></p><p>A company that has employees has to withhold tax before paying the employees and to pay it to the tax administration the month after the salary is paid. The rate depends on the employee salary, as listed below.</p><p>Monthly salary (Riels) Rate:</p><p>0 â 1,200,000Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  0%</p><p>1,200,001 â 2,000,000Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  5%</p><p>2,000,001 â 8,500,000Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  10%</p><p>8,500,001 â 12,500,000Â  Â  Â  Â  15%</p><p>12,500,001 â upwardsÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  20%</p><p>You can download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gdt.project.salarytax2018&amp;hl=en\">Salary Tax 2018 App</a> here, it can calculate your salary tax</p><p><strong>5. Public Lighting Tax</strong></p><p>This is a tax on all alcohol and cigarettes. The rate is 3% of all sales.</p><p><strong>NSSF Rates</strong></p><p>There are two contributions for the National Social Security Fund that are to be made each month by the employer.</p><p><strong>The Occupational Risk Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for occupational risk is 0.8% of the workers gross wage.</p><p><strong>The Health Care Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for the Health Care Scheme is 2.6% of the workers gross wage.</p><p>All workers are to be registered with the NSSF within 3 days of beginning employment.</p><p>NSSF payment deadline: 15<sup>th</sup> of each month</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '1946803ddf3c6a1e77806b557d8935cb', '', NULL);
