ent before 2019 is entitled to receive two payments in June; 1 back pay payment of 15 days and one seniority payment of 7.5 days of wages.</p><p>The back pay of seniority payments begins in 2019 with the first payment due in June 2019.</p><p><strong>Non-TGF Industry</strong></p><p>For companies not in the TGF industry the back pay of seniority payments are equal to 6 days of wages per year of employment (to a maximum of 6 months). The timing of these payments are 3 days in June and 3 days in December.</p><p>For the non-TGF industry, the back pay has been delayed until December 2021.</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '8c3401dc8a1b364681da3e8e92828bd9', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6765', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - d84c3576de069de25bdc733c0e2324bd', '<p><strong>Six Reasons Why You Should Register?Â </strong></p><p><strong>Peace of Mind</strong></p><p>One of the most common reasons why businesses come to us to register, is for peace of mind. Having an unregistered business is a constant concern for business owners, as that face the risk of fees and penalties when operating an unregistered business. These fees and penalties vary from monetary fines to the closing down of your business.</p><p><strong>Access to Markets</strong></p><p>The second most common reason why businesses come to us, is because they have just been turned down by a large customer because they were not registered. Registering your business means you will be more likely to access large contracts and customers and grow your business.</p><p>Example: a large client of your business wants you to supply your product to them, but they need to have an invoice with VAT.Â  This is because otherwise registered businesses will have to pay withholding tax on their purchases with is 15% compared with VAT which is 10% and they can offset.</p><p><strong>Improved Access to Finance</strong></p><p>Unless you own land that you can use as collateral, accessing finance from a financial institution can be very difficult for small and medium business owners, this becomes much more difficult if you are not registered. Most banks and investment firms will not invest or loan money to a business that is not registered.</p><p><strong>Improved ability to sell</strong></p><p>If you are looking to sell your business, it becomes much easier if it is registered as it is clear what the buyer is buying, it is legally protected and there are verifiable financial records. If you are not registered, you may not be able to sell as easily or for as much as the business is worth.</p><p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p><p>Through registration, your name and business is protected, you will have legal ways of fighting any business that copies your product or branding.</p><p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p><p>Being an ethical business means protecting your employees through labour rights. By registering you are required to pay NSSF on the behalf of staff, provide fair contracts, and provide annual leave and sick leave. This means that your employees will have job security and feel protected, not only is this good for your employees but is also the basis of a great staff culture and staff retention.</p><p>There are many reasons why you should register your business, but these six reasons are the most common reasons we see at Ngeay Ngeay. If you need help registering, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@ngeayngeay.co\">admin@ngeayngeay.co</a></p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '5b84ca5bcf1dc94331623aa8569fba37', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6766', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 773f735f579ccc69847cb77fef14f2fa', '<p><strong>Six Reasons Why You Should Register?Â </strong></p><p><strong>Peace of Mind</strong></p><p>One of the most common reasons why businesses come to us to register, is for peace of mind. Having an unregistered business is a constant concern for business owners, as that face the risk of fees and penalties when operating an unregistered business. These fees and penalties vary from monetary fines to the closing down of your business.</p><p><strong>Access to MarketsÂ </strong></p><p>The second most common reason why businesses come to us, is because they have just been turned down by a large customer because they were not registered. Registering your business means you will be more likely to access large contracts and customers and grow your business.</p><p>Example: a large client of your business wants you to supply your product to them, but they need to have an invoice with VAT.Â  This is because otherwise registered businesses will have to pay withholding tax on their purchases with is 15% compared with VAT which is 10% and they can offset.</p><p><strong>Improved Access to Finance</strong></p><p>Unless you own land that you can use as collateral, accessing finance from a financial institution can be very difficult for small and medium business owners, this becomes much more difficult if you are not registered. Most banks and investment firms will not invest or loan money to a business that is not registered.</p><p><strong>Improved ability to sell</strong></p><p>If you are looking to sell your business, it becomes much easier if it is registered as it is clear what the buyer is buying, it is legally protected and there are verifiable financial records. If you are not registered, you may not be able to sell as easily or for as much as the business is worth.</p><p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p><p>Through registration, your name and business is protected, you will have legal ways of fighting any business that copies your product or branding.</p><p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p><p>Being an ethical business means protecting your employees through labour rights. By registering you are required to pay NSSF on the behalf of staff, provide fair contracts, and provide annual leave and sick leave. This means that your employees will have job security and feel protected, not only is this good for your employees but is also the basis of a great staff culture and staff retention.</p><p>There are many reasons why you should register your business, but these six reasons are the most common reasons we see at Ngeay Ngeay. If you need help registering, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@ngeayngeay.co\">admin@ngeayngeay.co</a></p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '44b09bc9730fd0e7591335946346aea7', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6767', 'en', 'elementor-1404', 'title-heading-53c7869b', 'The Importance of Time Management', '64', '1', 'h2', 'LINE', 'Heading', '0', '', '8d4172bd76bb4b4726b9933de8949da2', 'optional', '5');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6768', 'en', 'elementor-1404', 'editor-text-editor-4cb0e071', '<p>Time is one of the most valuable assets we have, and everyone has the same amount, whether you are a millionaire or an executive of a large corporation you still only have 24 hours a day just like everybody.Â </p>', '64', '2', '', 'VISUAL', 'Text editor', '0', '', 'bdea6fceed0664df948b9e1a48bf4974', 'optional', '40');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('6769', 'en', 'elementor-1404', 'editor-text-editor-3123be4', '<p>This means that if you can utilise your time better you have an automatic advantage over other people and can achieve more, be more relaxed and be able to spend more time with the people most important to you.</p><p>Â </p><p>To be able to be better at time management it is important to understand why it is so valuable. Here are 3 reasons why time management is crucial to your success and well-being:</p><ol><li>Better results with less effort</li></ol><p>When you really master time management, you improve your ability to focusing on a task. When you can really focus on a task and not get distracted with Facebook, emails, chats, or other distractions you can achieve an astonishing amount of work in a short amount of time. The result? Improved results, with much less effort.</p><ol start=\"2\"><li>Better Decision making</li></ol><p>When you are able to manage your time effectively, your stress levels are reduced significantly. No more thinking, I need to thisâ¦ I need to do thatâ¦. With great time management, you know what needs to be done and know how to focus on getting it done. Without getting too technical, no matter how logical we think our decisions are, every decision we make has an emotional component to it. When we have less stress, we are able to make clearer decisions as our emotions are more stable. For more information about decision making and emotions you can read Thinking Fast and Slow by Daniel Kahneman.</p><ol start=\"3\"><li>More time with family &amp; friends</li></ol><p>Lastly, with better time management you are able to spend more time with your family and friends and doing activities that you enjoy. Better time management means less time working as you are able to achieve more in less time, this means you are able to switch off and spend more time playing sport, relaxing and spending time with the people most important to you.</p><p>Listen to Sreypov talk about how improving her time management has helped her business.</p>', '64', '3', '', 'VISUAL', 'Text editor', '0', '', '03d10870df29e385a0f33d44d2ae48dd', 'optional', '325');
