INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11596', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 9df3f9d7e8c7cf146ccd0490c9e59189', '<p><strong>Vision vs Mission</strong></p><p>The difference between vision and mission statements can get confusing, the easiest way to think about them, is the mission is what you are doing today, and the vision is where you want to go.</p><p><strong>Your Vision</strong></p><p>So how do you write a vision statement? Letâs be honest, writing a vision statement is HARD. How do you put into one sentence everything you want to achieve with your business? And how do you make it inspiring and catchy?</p><ol><li>Think about what you want the business to achieve, think BIG.</li><li>Keep it short â one or two sentences</li><li>Make it clear, do not use jargon or words that can be interpreted differently</li><li>Think about what is the result of what you do? An example: CafÃ© â putting a smile on the face of every customer</li><li>There needs to me a source of measurement, but very broad. Every customer, every small business in Phnom Penh, etc.</li><li>Add some imagery. Smiling customer, a computer on a desk.</li></ol><p>These steps will help you get started but be prepared to put in some time getting your vision right. Work with your team to come up with a vision, everyone cares about.</p><p>Need help writing your vision? <a href=\"http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/contact-us/\">Contact Us</a> here.</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'e167551c3a9f918ce7442af8f78525df', '', NULL);
