INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11614', 'en', 'elementor-1958', 'editor-text-editor-3123be4', '<p>With any young business, cashflow is one of the most important things to understand well. Cashflow is one of the most common reasons that a business will shutdown, sometimes they are even profitable businesses but they if they do manage their cash properly they can go out of business. It is critical that you understand and can track your cashflow.</p><p><strong>Budgets</strong></p><p>The business budget for a small business is most commonly used when starting your business or going through a significant expansion. Establishing how much capital is needed to either start your business or expand is crucial, because if you do not have enough capital at the start, you can potentially run out of money before your business is profitable. We have a budget template here for you to calculate how much capital you will need to start your business.</p><p>To calculate the capital needed you will need to know:</p><ul><li>Estimated start-up expenses</li><li>Estimated monthly revenue for the next 6 months</li><li>Estimated monthly expenses for the next 6 months</li></ul><p>Input all of these into the template and it will provide an estimated amount of capital needed, included in the budget is some buffer to allow for errors in your estimates.</p><p>Â </p>', '83', '3', '', 'VISUAL', 'Text editor', '0', '', 'fa46d19db1d9620fa30888760f032183', 'optional', '198');
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11615', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 859fb7d75ebbc7c79a9f7715c514b578', '<p>With any young business, cashflow is one of the most important things to understand well. Cashflow is one of the most common reasons that a business will shutdown, sometimes they are even profitable businesses but they if they do manage their cash properly they can go out of business. It is critical that you understand and can track your cashflow.</p><p><strong>Budgets</strong></p><p>The business budget for a small business is most commonly used when starting your business or going through a significant expansion. Establishing how much capital is needed to either start your business or expand is crucial, because if you do not have enough capital at the start, you can potentially run out of money before your business is profitable. We have a budget template here for you to calculate how much capital you will need to start your business.</p><p>To calculate the capital needed you will need to know:</p><ul><li>Estimated start-up expenses</li><li>Estimated monthly revenue for the next 6 months</li><li>Estimated monthly expenses for the next 6 months</li></ul><p>Input all of these into the template and it will provide an estimated amount of capital needed, included in the budget is some buffer to allow for errors in your estimates.</p><p>Â </p><p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'b33e5022fd87a6928a5c7f4cb1d3b403', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11616', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 833384442df0a36cce2d980c98d3d37c', '<p>With any young business, cashflow is one of the most important things to understand well. Cashflow is one of the most common reasons that a business will shutdown, sometimes they are even profitable businesses but they if they do manage their cash properly they can go out of business. It is critical that you understand and can track your cashflow.</p><p><strong>Budgets</strong></p><p>The business budget for a small business is most commonly used when starting your business or going through a significant expansion. Establishing how much capital is needed to either start your business or expand is crucial, because if you do not have enough capital at the start, you can potentially run out of money before your business is profitable. We have a budget template here for you to calculate how much capital you will need to start your business.</p><p>To calculate the capital needed you will need to know:</p><ul><li>Estimated start-up expenses</li><li>Estimated monthly revenue for the next 6 months</li><li>Estimated monthly expenses for the next 6 months</li></ul><p>Input all of these into the template and it will provide an estimated amount of capital needed, included in the budget is some buffer to allow for errors in your estimates.</p><p><strong>Cashflow</strong></p><p>The cashflow forecast template, can be found here. It includes a 12-week cashflow and a 12-month cashflow, some businesses will require both, for others it will be more appropriate to do one or the other, this will depend on the cashflows of your business.</p><p>It is important when using this template that you ensure the numbers you put in are timed for you either receive or pay the money, not when you are given the invoice or when you make the sale.</p><p>The cashflow forecast should be updated regularly, to ensure that if are having times when you may run out of cash that you can plan accordingly, by delaying bill payments, getting short term loans or chasing up invoices that need to be paid to you.</p><p>By using both the budget template and cashflow template you can get a better handle on how you are spending your money and whether you will have enough money to pay your bills.</p><p>Â </p><p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '4b6fe7020a42ddad1ffaf31fdbc20c2d', '', NULL);
