INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11659', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 6d699e77ed49e50965111df2b71d035c', '<p>ááINSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11660', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 8d6c6d21a3bff5ad28bd1e11a8e6a087', '<p><strong><span lang=\"KHM\" style=\"font-family: \'Khmer OS\';\">áááá¾áááá¶áááááá¶ááááá¶áááááá½áááááá¢ááá</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang=\"KHM\" style=\"font-family: \'Khmer OS\';\">áá¶áá·ááINSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11661', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - a8680d059617fe9d5735002b65d91691', '<p>The rate of unregistered businesses is very high in Cambodia. TheÂ Cambodian government has been addressing this issue in recent years and working to make the registration process easier and cheaper. But why should you register?</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '814c856cde6d778752ce1474b04cc206', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11662', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - c82689767f11b261b238ebd80a845db5', '<p><strong>Six Reasons Why You Should Register?Â </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Peace of Mind</strong></p>\n<p>One of the most common reasons why businesses come to us to register, is for peace of mind. Having an unregistered business is a constant concern for business owners, as that face the risk of fees and penalties when operating an unregistered business. These fees and penalties vary from monetary fines to the closing down of your business.</p>\n<p><strong>Access to MarketsÂ </strong></p>\n<p>The second most common reason why businesses come to us, is because they have just been turned down by a large customer because they were not registered. Registering your business means you will be more likely to access large contracts and customers and grow your business.</p>\n<p>Example: a large client of your business wants you to supply your product to them, but they need to have an invoice with VAT.Â  This is because otherwise registered businesses will have to pay withholding tax on their purchases with is 15% compared with VAT which is 10% and they can offset.</p>\n<p><strong>Improved Access to Finance</strong></p>\n<p>Unless you own land that you can use as collateral, accessing finance from a financial institution can be very difficult for small and medium business owners, this becomes much more difficult if you are not registered. Most banks and investment firms will not invest or loan money to a business that is not registered.</p>\n<p><strong>Improved ability to sell</strong></p>\n<p>If you are looking to sell your business, it becomes much easier if it is registered as it is clear what the buyer is buying, it is legally protected and there are verifiable financial records. If you are not registered, you may not be able to sell as easily or for as much as the business is worth.</p>\n<p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p>\n<p>Through registration, your name and business is protected, you will have legal ways of fighting any business that copies your product or branding.</p>\n<p><strong>Protect your business</strong></p>\n<p>Being an ethical business means protecting your employees through labour rights. By registering you are required to pay NSSF on the behalf of staff, provide fair contracts, and provide annual leave and sick leave. This means that your employees will have job security and feel protected, not only is this good for your employees but is also the basis of a great staff culture and staff retention.</p>\n<p>There are many reasons why you should register your business, but these six reasons are the most common reasons we see at Ngeay Ngeay. If you need help registering, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@ngeayngeay.co\">admin@ngeayngeay.co</a></p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '6ca849626c415ca73ac4b8f39d51e667', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11663', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 022864e63db0b30ffb47acf310f3907b', '<p>What you need to know to register a business in Cambodia</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '0f5e77aa5044451a976a5fe718cc44a1', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11664', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - a2c4ee25b3377a18679b16904b760e54', '<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'd7cb5c099e7bae89151c1c63a9da09c2', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11665', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - fcfe34c2193f784a9754bff2bdabd6c4', '<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p>\n<p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p>\n<p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'fbe093bccccfdfe43c79e444441f8be3', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11666', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 702f7ec082b6e99ccbc429c6bd786d91', '<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p>\n<p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p>\n<p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p>\n<p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the companyâs debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p>\n<p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p>\n<p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. Itâs a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li>\n<li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li>\n<li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'b3350c0828581361471465b94a18d52e', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11667', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - c3c3870d0a3a0d78f6efe6c21c3bc3bc', '<p>Everything you need to know to be compliant with the Cambodian Law</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', 'c1883120a358749ef30991c6fac18e6a', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11668', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - fa5498f3b5881df0cf1d6cc230a97010', '<p>áá¶ááINSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11669', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 7b767d285db8534898391a0c35a70223', '<p>áá¶ááINSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11670', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - e902dd60e436166c7be5c4da19f3cc57', '<p>áá¶ááááá¶áááá¼áá ááá»áááá¶ááINSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11673', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 212056e2737abf004055aeef1c6f9efa', '<p><strong>Vision vs Mission</strong></p><p>The difference between vision and mission statements can get confusing, the easiest way to think about them, is the mission is what you are doing today, and the vision is where you want to go.</p><p><strong>Your Vision</strong></p><p>So how do you write a vision statement? Letâs be honest, writing a vision statement is HARD. How do you put into one sentence everything you want to achieve with your business? And how do you make it inspiring and catchy?</p><ol><li>Think about what you want the business to achieve, think BIG.</li><li>Keep it short â one or two sentences</li><li>Make it clear, do not use jargon or words that can be interpreted differently</li><li>Think about what is the result of what you do? An example: CafÃ© â putting a smile on the face of every customer</li><li>There needs to me a source of measurement, but very broad. Every customer, every small business in Phnom Penh, etc.</li><li>Add some imagery. Smiling customer, a computer on a desk.</li></ol><p>These steps will help you get started but be prepared to put in some time getting your vision right. Work with your team to come up with a vision, everyone cares about.</p><p>Need help writing your vision? <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contact-us/\">Contact Us</a> here.</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '9b6a25077143e6998f72fa86ca245078', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11674', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - f63f2e1059e66663633726bd55e0b95f', '<p><strong>Seniority payments vs Severance Payments</strong></p><p>There are now two terms for severance payments in the updated Labour Law, seniority payments and severance payments. Severance payments refer to <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contracts/\">Fixed Duration contracts</a> (FDC). Seniority payments refer to <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contracts/\">Unfixed Duration contracts</a> (UDC).</p><p><strong>Severance Payments (Fixed Duration Contracts)</strong></p><p>For employees under fixed duration contracts, a severance pay of 5% of the total wages due throughout the contract must be paid at the completion or termination of the contract.</p><p><strong>Seniority Payments (Unfixed Duration Contracts)</strong></p><p>Employees on unfixed duration contracts are entitled to seniority payments equal to 15 days of wages and fringe benefits per year. This is to be made over two payments over the year:</p><p>1<sup>st</sup> payment (June): 7.5 days of wages and fringe benefits to be paid each year</p><p>2<sup>nd</sup> payment: (December): 7.5 days of wages and fringe benefits to be paid each year</p><p><strong>Back Pay of Seniority Payments</strong></p><p>Employees who have been employed prior to 2019 are entitled to back pay of seniority payments for the course of their employment, however this is capped at a maximum of 6 month of the average base wage in each year of employment.</p><p>For the non-TGF industry, the back pay has been delayed until December 2021.</p><p><strong>Textile, Garment and Footwear (TGF) Industry</strong></p><p>For the textile, garment and footwear (TGF) manufacturing industry, employees are entitled to 30 days of back pay each year (to a maximum of 6 months).</p><p>Back pay is to be paid in two installments over the course of the year; therefore an employee that commenced employment before 2019 is entitled to receive two payments in June; 1 back pay payment of 15 days and one seniority payment of 7.5 days of wages.</p><p>The back pay of seniority payments begins in 2019 with the first payment due in June 2019.</p><p><strong>Non-TGF Industry</strong></p><p>For companies not in the TGF industry the back pay of seniority payments are equal to 6 days of wages per year of employment (to a maximum of 6 months). The timing of these payments are 3 days in June and 3 days in December.</p><p>For the non-TGF industry, the back pay has been delayed until December 2021.</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '4970e576a5263ae51c1fd27f94289561', '', NULL);
