INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11677', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - d2732211302e01b0f32d47099fd16d30', '<p><strong>Small Taxpayers (Sole Proprietors &amp; Partnerships)</strong></p><p>The requirements for small taxpayers are significantly less than they are for medium and large taxpayers. Small Taxpayers are required to have three books:</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Expenses-Day-Book-updated.xlsx\"><strong><em>Expenses Day Book</em></strong></a></p><p>This is the gathering of all the operational expenses made by the company, so basically everything that it buys. It can refer to: goods or services, raw materials, employee wages, utility billsâ¦. This record has to be completed daily.</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sales-Day-Book.xlsx\"><strong><em>Sales Day Book</em></strong></a></p><p>The Sales day book, also a daily record, refers to all the goods and services sold by the company.</p><p><strong><em><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Ngeay-Ngeay-Inventory-template.xlsx\">Inventory Book</a></em></strong></p><p>The inventory book is the count of the inventory of the business.</p><p>Other suggested but not legally required books are:</p><p><strong><em>Accounts Receivable</em></strong></p><p>This is any money that is owed to you</p><p><strong><em>Accounts Payable</em></strong></p><p>This is any money that you owe</p><p><strong><em>Assets Book</em></strong></p><p>Any equipment, furniture or machinery you buy that is over $100</p><p><strong>Medium &amp; Large Taxpayers</strong></p><p>As the tax filing that is required for medium and large taxpayers is significantly more complex than it is for small taxpayers we strongly recommend that you use official accounting procedures such as CIFRS and use a system such as Quickbooks, Xero or Banhji.</p><p>If you are new to book keeping and accounting, we recommend that you hire a professional to help you with these. See here.</p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '1f25cfd32b766c723d038339787a45cb', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `nge_icl_strings` VALUES('11678', 'en', 'Widgets', 'widget body - 45c4788bd735b71543cfadfb6b0af46e', '<p>Each month you will have to pay your taxes, this includes your value added tax (VAT), tax on salary, minimum tax on profit, withholding tax and public lighting tax. Additionally you will need to pay your NSSF fees (see here).</p><p>Filing and payment of taxes in Cambodia for medium and large taxpayers is quite complex, we highly recommend that you hire a professional to assist you in this process. However, it is important you understand the basic process, as its your responsibility to ensure that all the taxes are paid correctly.</p><p>For small taxpayers (sole proprietors and partnerships), you only need to fill out one form. The instructions are found on the second page of the form.</p><p>For medium and large taxpayers, there are multiple forms and evidence that is required.</p><p>To file your taxes you need to download the appropriate forms found here. You will need to fill out all the forms and provide the necessary evidence, you need to hand these forms in, with payment to your local tax department for your Khan. Monthly taxes are due on the 20<sup>th</sup> of each month.</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/tax-nssf-rates/\">For the latest tax rates, see here.</a></p>', NULL, NULL, '', 'LINE', NULL, '0', '', '1462fabb9a4fa37add476dbc2948c6b1', '', NULL);
